    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-21T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-21T06:00:00-05:00" n="65"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d65">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/3568</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Denmark</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_EMF1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Egan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-21T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 21, 1917, 12 noon</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received March 22, 8 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>513. Hamburg <hi rend="italic">Fremdenblatt</hi>, March 20, says that as a result
                    of the Chancellor’s recent speech in regard to the contemplated alteration in
                    the system of election in Prussia after the war the Socialist leader Scheidemann
                    published an article in <hi rend="italic">Vorwärts</hi> in which he, while
                    referring to the revolution in Russia, strongly urges that a bill be placed
                    immediately before the Reichstag granting the population of Prussia equal
                    suffrage for electing members to the Reichstag. The <hi rend="italic"
                        >Fremdenblatt</hi> states that the article of Scheidemann has caused the
                    greatest sensation in political circles in Berlin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_EMF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Egan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
